title: You COULD go out and spend $120+ on a graphing calculator...
comment: ...or you could spend the chump change that this wonderful dev is asking for the best TI emulator on the market.  I don't think they're allowed to link to ROMs in the description, but all TI calculator operating system files (which this emulator reads) are available FOR FREE on TI's website.  Just Google it.  They're incredibly small files too, in case you were wondering.  Then it's just a matter of telling this app where the file is, and boom.  Fully functioning TI-89 Titanium.  Voyage 200.  TI-92 Plus.  It's about as fully featured an emulator as one could ask for and more, including the ability to change the screen colors and install apps to the virtual calculators.  Do yourselves a favor people:  get this if you need a calculator.

comment: The whole reason I bought the calculator was because I liked that it didn't need my autobiography as a condition of purchase. You going to look us up on Facebook or something? Please reconsider.

IDs are needed by many TI89 applications that require a license key to be installed.
Graph89 does use an internet connection.

title: The best thing since an actual TI-89
comment: They do not make the TI-89 anymore, and I hate the TI-89 Titanium.  I have bought several 89's off eBay/Craigslist just to make sure I horde enough to cover me for the rest of my life.  Now I have THIS.  This thing is SLICK.  As for the ROM, the instructions do not give much detail before you down load it.  When you install and open it, you go to settings and then navigate to the folder where your ROM is located (I just have it on the SD card).  As for getting the ROM off your old calculator, I have no idea how to do that.  You can download the latest ROM's straight from TI's website.  Go to the downloads/updates section and look for the 89 or 89 Titanium.
Love it

title: great app but donate version nothing special
comment: i have used the graph 89 free program for some time now, but just like my calculator some Taylor calculations take some considerable time to solve. i noticed the cpu speed increase on the donate version to speed up processing, and with that in mind i purchased it. i increased the cpu to 250% the max it will go, entered in the Taylor calculation and waited, and waited, and waited. then the answer came up. wow it took a long time to solve, so i timed them both the free vs the donate, and wouldn't you know it, they were the same. this disappointed me, basically i all you get with this version is the skins which do nothing for me. the app is the best calculator app out there but the promised speed increase is false. if this is a problem and should work it needs to be fixed.
Of course it also depends on the speed of your android device. But generally speaking, with what's considered normal speed nowdays, Graph89 is about 2-3 times faster than the actual calculator.
